steps.instruction:
### Crust
- Preheat oven to 350F
- Crush the pretzels fine enough to make the crust
- Combine the crushed pretzels and melted butter
- Press the mixture onto the bottom and 1 inch up the sides of a 10 inch spring-form pan.
- Put the pan into a baking sheet
- Put baking sheet with pan into oven for 5 minutes
- Let it cool completely on a wire rack

### Cheese Cake
- In a large bowl combine room temperature creme cheese and sugar until smooth
- Add in 3/4 of a cup of creamy peanut butter and 2 teaspoons of vanilla extract and mix well
- Add in the 3 eggs and beat on low until combined
- Pour mixture over the crust
- Return it to the baking sheet
- Bake at 350F for 50 to 55 minutes, or until the center is almost set
- Remove when done and let it sit for 15 minutes (leave oven on)

### Topping
- In  a small bowl combine 1 cup of sour creme and 3 tablespoons of creamy peanut butter and 1/2 cup of sugar
- Spread topping over filling
- Finely chop 1/2 cup of the unsalted peanuts
- Sprinkle over the top of the topping
- Bake for 5 minutes
- Take out when done, let cool for at least 10 minutes 
- Run a knife around the edge of the pan to loosen the cake
- Let cool for 1 hour

### Last Steps
- Put in fridge overnight
- Remove pan when serving
- Refrigerate leftovers
